g.text: Conditions are used to control the creation of resources or outputs based on conditions you specify.
- Conditions commonly used are Environment (dev/test/prod), AWS Region, etc.
Conditions are useful when you want to deploy resources differently based on parameters or environmental factors
- Conditions are declared in the "Conditions" section of a CloudFormation template.
- You can use them in "Resources", "Outputs", and "Metadata" sections to decide when something should be
- Common condition functions include: Fn::Equals, Fn:If, Fn:Not, Fn:Or, Fn:And
